data.text:
Band Name: Tommy Tutone

Website: Tutone.com

Members: Tommy Heath, lead vocals, performing with the local rhythm section of Bobby Salamone, drums, and Victor Castaneda, bass and vocals. “They’ve played with me in many gigs from Detroit to Minneapolis,” Heath said.

City based in: Portland, Ore.

Formed in: 1977

Name inspired by: “My personal nickname from my love of two-tone 54 Chevy’s,” Heath said.

We sound like: No one else sings like Tommy Tutone. He is inspired by Van Morrison, ‘60s soul, country, and ‘50s rockabilly.

Known for: The hit “867-5309/Jenny,” which peaked at No. 4 in 1982 going gold on the Billboard Hot 100.

Coolest story so far from a show: “My first big concert ever was in 1980 opening for Tom Petty at the Red Rocks amphitheater in Colorado,” Heath said.
